autograd
t.requires_grad, t.requires_grad_(), t.backward(tensor), t.grad, t.grad_fn
with torch.no_grad(): to not track the history

tensor
tensor.view() to reshape the tensor

torch.max(tensor, dim) return max value of each row in the given dim, also return the index of max in each row 

{torch.utils.data.TensorDataset(data, label)} to create a dataset(with label) that can be resoluted by {torch.utils.data.DataLoader}
